{
  "_comment": "TEMPLATE for backend:\"service\" on OPENCODE (dev-loop P8 portability; see docs/PORTABILITY.md). Merge the `mcp` entry into your opencode config (e.g. ~/.config/opencode/config.json or a repo-local opencode.json). Replace <ABS-PATH-TO-dev-loop> and the absolute db path. ⚠️ VERIFY against your installed opencode version: (1) the exact `mcp` server schema (this uses type:\"local\" + a command ARRAY + an `environment` map — confirm), and (2) whether opencode PROPAGATES THE LAUNCHING PROCESS ENV to the MCP subprocess. Per-pane identity is load-bearing: DEVLOOP_ACTOR differs per agent pane, so it CANNOT live in this shared file — it must ride the process env each pane's launcher exports before `opencode`. CONFIRM with the identity gate (docs/PORTABILITY.md): `DEVLOOP_ACTOR=dev opencode run \"call the dev-loop-hub whoami tool and print only the actor\"` → must print \"dev\" (not \"operator\"); else opencode is NOT propagating per-pane identity → do not onboard until fixed.",
  "mcp": {
    "dev-loop-hub": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": ["node", "<ABS-PATH-TO-dev-loop>/hub/src/server.ts"],
      "environment": {
        "DEVLOOP_PROJECT": "",
        "DEVLOOP_HUB_DB": "/ABSOLUTE/PATH/.dev-loop/hub.db"
      },
      "_DEVLOOP_PROJECT_note": "literal empty (NOT shell-expanded here) ⇒ the hub auto-resolves the project from the spawned process's cwd (DL-13); set a non-empty value to pin one explicitly, or omit the key.",
      "_shim_note": "OPT-IN daemon transport (DL-55): to route the core ticket tools through the running daemon instead of opening hub.db directly, change the command's 2nd element to `<ABS-PATH-TO-dev-loop>/hub/src/shim.ts` (from `.../src/server.ts`). REQUIRES the per-project daemon up + settings_json.hub.transport=\"daemon\" (DL-43); the shim discovers the port from the DL-41 runfile `~/.dev-loop/daemon-<key>.json` (override DEVLOOP_HUB_PORT), never 8787. Scope: the 5 core ticket tools + whoami — doc.*/topic.*/channel.* still need server.ts.",
      "enabled": true
    }
  }
}
